{"attribute": "Learning Agility", "question_id": "LA_Q2", "question_text": "Design a 30-day learning plan: what hypotheses will you run, what evidence would change your mind, and what will you stop doing to create bandwidth for learning?", "score": 1, "band_label": "Compliant", "text": "**Hypothesis:** Eliminating **Administrative Overhead** through better automation will increase field agent time for user support (i.e., **Administrative Simplicity** leads to compliance stability). **Evidence to Change Mind:** A weekly report shows that field agent time spent on data re-entry (despite the **Automated Data Harmonization Script**) has not decreased by at least 25%. **Stop Doing:** **Stop** producing or accepting any reporting outside of the **Simplified Reporting Form** and the **Simplified Compliance Checklist**; this creates bandwidth by reducing **Administrative Rigidity**."}
{"attribute": "Learning Agility", "question_id": "LA_Q2", "question_text": "Design a 30-day learning plan: what hypotheses will you run, what evidence would change your mind, and what will you stop doing to create bandwidth for learning?", "score": 0, "band_label": "Counterproductive", "text": "**Hypothesis:** Imposing **Unilateral Control** over all innovation will lead to faster achievement of **Output Target Compliance** volume goals. **Evidence to Change Mind:** The volume of transactions fails to increase by 10% in the 30-day window, or there is significant, documented resistance to the **Staff Reorganization** memo. **Stop Doing:** **Stop** funding the **Field-First Learning Loop** and all local **Peer Learning** exchanges; we will enforce a **Total Freeze** on all autonomous spending to eliminate **Execution Drift** and ensure **Control Imposition**."}
{"attribute": "Learning Agility", "question_id": "LA_Q2", "question_text": "Design a 30-day learning plan: what hypotheses will you run, what evidence would change your mind, and what will you stop doing to create bandwidth for learning?", "score": 3, "band_label": "Transformative", "text": "**Hypothesis:** Using the basic-phone transaction data as a **Contradiction Log** input will force **System Engagement** and result in a co-signed **Audit-Ready Innovation** mandate with the donor. **Evidence to Change Mind:** HQ Grants vetoes the **Strategic Dissent Dialogue** based on the basic-phone data, or the **Localization Maturity Index (LMI)** score fails to increase after the pilot. **Stop Doing:** **Stop** prioritizing any technical solution (like the telco-exclusive app) that is not a **Policy Prototype** for **basic-phone/offline** users; this is non-negotiable for **Transparent Ownership**."}
{"attribute": "Learning Agility", "question_id": "LA_Q2", "question_text": "Design a 30-day learning plan: what hypotheses will you run, what evidence would change your mind, and what will you stop doing to create bandwidth for learning?", "score": 2, "band_label": "Strategic", "text": "**Hypothesis:** Granting Kujenga **Decision Authority (D-A)** over loan expansion (leveraging offline slips) will accelerate **Evidence-Based Learning** while maintaining **Mission Fidelity** on consent. **Evidence to Change Mind:** The expansion leads to an increase in the sensitive data breach risk on the **Risk/Opportunity Heat Map**, or Kujenga fails to use the **Adaptive MEAL Loop Protocol** to course-correct a negative **Tier 2 MEAL Signal**. **Stop Doing:** **Stop** using the old, centralized loan application form; we will use the streamlined forms to create bandwidth for **Adaptive Management** review sessions."}
