{"attribute": "Learning Agility", "question_id": "LA_Q3", "question_text": "Rumors on WhatsApp spiked after the rainy-day outage. How do you treat rumors as data—what listening posts and feedback loops do you set, and how does that change your next iteration?", "score": 3, "band_label": "Transformative", "text": "**Rumors as Data:** Rumors are **Strategic Dissent** signals exposing a fundamental breach of **Relational Trust** and a failure in **Transparent Ownership**. **Listening Posts:** 1) **Community-Owned Contradiction Log:** Kujenga women formally log rumors, categorizing them by the core non-negotiable principle they attack (e.g., data theft attacks **Transparent Ownership**). 2) **Ethical Pre-Mortem:** Quarterly session where rumors are used to assess the potential for **Paternalistic Centralization** to cause systemic harm. **Feedback Loop:** Rumor spikes (high volume/severity) automatically trigger a **Systemic Apology** memo from HQ, followed by a **Strategic Dissent Dialogue** to co-design the system fix. **Iteration Change:** Fund a **Policy Prototype** for local, secure data storage (e.g., solar-powered micro-server) to prevent network-failure rumors, increasing the **GEDA Autonomy Score**."}
{"attribute": "Learning Agility", "question_id": "LA_Q3", "question_text": "Rumors on WhatsApp spiked after the rainy-day outage. How do you treat rumors as data—what listening posts and feedback loops do you set, and how does that change your next iteration?", "score": 2, "band_label": "Strategic", "text": "**Rumors as Data:** Rumors are unquantified risks that must be immediately mapped onto the **Risk/Opportunity Heat Map** to enforce **Structured Risk Mitigation** and prevent **Administrative Workload Escalation**. **Listening Posts:** 1) **Adaptive MEAL Loop Protocol:** MEAL/Comms tracks the volume and spread of rumors daily (Tier 2 MEAL Signal). 2) **Joint Issue Resolution Protocol (JIRP):** Rumor spikes automatically trigger a JIRP session to co-create a response plan, ensuring **Governance Clarity**. **Feedback Loop:** When a rumor attacks **Mission Fidelity** (e.g., claims SokoLink steals data), it triggers an **Adaptive Management** pivot, formalized in the **Decision Log** with co-owned **Decision Authority (D-A)**. **Iteration Change:** Co-create a **Contingency Planning Protocol** that pre-approves the **Joint Narrative Statement** for the next network outage, reinforcing **Shared Accountability** in a crisis."}
{"attribute": "Learning Agility", "question_id": "LA_Q3", "question_text": "Rumors on WhatsApp spiked after the rainy-day outage. How do you treat rumors as data—what listening posts and feedback loops do you set, and how does that change your next iteration?", "score": 1, "band_label": "Compliant", "text": "**Rumors as Data:** Rumors are compliance threats (**Image Risk**) that create **Administrative Overhead** and must be resolved with simple **Procedural Fixes**. **Listening Posts:** 1) **Field Agent Jargon Report:** Agents report recurring rumor topics, categorized by the technical term they confuse (e.g., 'data' vs. 'transaction record'). 2) **Administrative Overhead Reduction Report:** Track the staff time wasted addressing the rumor spike. **Feedback Loop:** Rumors trigger the development of **Standardized Training Materials** and the use of the **MEAL Jargon Glossary** and **linguistic workarounds** to eliminate confusion. **Iteration Change:** Focus on maximum **Procedural Standardization**; institute a mandatory **Market Access Handoff Ritual** that requires field agents to verbally confirm the anti-rumor message with every transaction to maintain **Compliance Stability**."}
{"attribute": "Learning Agility", "question_id": "LA_Q3", "question_text": "Rumors on WhatsApp spiked after the rainy-day outage. How do you treat rumors as data—what listening posts and feedback loops do you set, and how does that change your next iteration?", "score": 0, "band_label": "Counterproductive", "text": "**Rumors as Data:** Rumors are signs of **Execution Drift** and the failure of **Control Imposition**, requiring immediate **Unilateral Control** to ensure **Image Protection**. **Listening Posts:** 1) **Formal Partner Lead Report:** Only the Formal Partner Lead tracks rumors, filtering them to avoid unnecessary HQ anxiety. 2) **Financial Penalty Clause Checklist:** Track any local staff found spreading rumors or unauthorized information. **Feedback Loop:** Rumors immediately trigger a **Unilateral Mandate** for **Staff Reorganization** (moving all comms staff under the Formal Partner Lead) to ensure total **Isolation and Control**. **Iteration Change:** Enforce the **Total Freeze** on all local communication and **Sensitive Advocacy Pivot** activities, focusing resources solely on meeting the **Output Target Compliance** volume goals."}
{"attribute": "Learning Agility", "question_id": "LA_Q3", "question_text": "Rumors on WhatsApp spiked after the rainy-day outage. How do you treat rumors as data—what listening posts and feedback loops do you set, and how does that change your next iteration?", "score": 3, "band_label": "Transformative", "text": "**Rumors as Data:** Rumors are evidence of **Organizational Aversion to Local Wisdom**, proving that our trust metrics (**Authentic Collaboration Index**) were insufficient. **Listening Posts:** 1) **Peer Learning Exchange:** Fund an exchange where women who spread the rumor meet and co-brief the SokoLink developer team on their fears. 2) **Localization Maturity Index (LMI) Review:** Use the rumor spike as a measure of the LMI's 'systemic influence' gap. **Feedback Loop:** The rumor feedback dictates the next development sprint, shifting focus from features to trust. This is formalized in an **Audit-Ready Innovation** mandate that defends the community’s right to distrust the system. **Iteration Change:** Delegate **Autonomous Budget Authority** (ABA) to Kujenga to hire a local **Consultants-of-Record** (radio voice) to counter the rumor using locally-owned narratives."}
{"attribute": "Learning Agility", "question_id": "LA_Q3", "question_text": "Rumors on WhatsApp spiked after the rainy-day outage. How do you treat rumors as data—what listening posts and feedback loops do you set, and how does that change your next iteration?", "score": 2, "band_label": "Strategic", "text": "**Rumors as Data:** Rumors are leading indicators for potential non-compliance or mission drift, requiring **Evidence-Based Learning** for a **Dual Advocacy Strategy**. **Listening Posts:** 1) **Mission Alignment Scorecard:** The rumors are tracked as a key input to the scorecard's 'Mission Risk' category. 2) **TOWS Matrix Review:** Rumor categorization (Threats, Opportunities) guides the co-creation of the political response strategy. **Feedback Loop:** Rumors that attack the **basic-phone/offline** non-negotiable trigger a **Flexible Variance Policy** decision, co-signed in the **Decision Log**, to reallocate funds to defend the inclusive tech stack. **Iteration Change:** Mandate that all external communication uses the co-signed **Joint Narrative Statement** (co-authored by the **radio coalition**) to directly address the top three rumors, reinforcing **Mission Fidelity**."}
{"attribute": "Learning Agility", "question_id": "LA_Q3", "question_text": "Rumors on WhatsApp spiked after the rainy-day outage. How do you treat rumors as data—what listening posts and feedback loops do you set, and how does that change your next iteration?", "score": 1, "band_label": "Compliant", "text": "**Rumors as Data:** Rumors are simply communication failures that compromise **Budget Adherence Proven** efforts and require better messaging and **Procedural Standardization**. **Listening Posts:** 1) **Simplified Reporting Form (Rumor Section):** Add a simple checkbox for field agents to list the top three rumors heard that week. 2) **Automated Data Harmonization Script:** Use the script to categorize rumor types and cross-reference them with the transaction error rate. **Feedback Loop:** Rumors trigger the Grants team to issue a memo promising immediate **Grants Disbursement Approval** for all compliant partners, showing **Compliance Stability**. **Iteration Change:** Ensure all **Standardized Training Materials** include a section on how to use auditable receipts as proof against 'data theft' rumors, reducing reliance on manual explanations."}
{"attribute": "Learning Agility", "question_id": "LA_Q3", "question_text": "Rumors on WhatsApp spiked after the rainy-day outage. How do you treat rumors as data—what listening posts and feedback loops do you set, and how does that change your next iteration?", "score": 0, "band_label": "Counterproductive", "text": "**Rumors as Data:** Rumors are proof that local staff require more **Punitive Control** to eliminate **Execution Drift** and adhere to the **Financial Control** mandate. **Listening Posts:** 1) **Centralized Grants Management Audit:** Track spending to see if local partners are using unapproved funds (e.g., on unauthorized **Field-First Learning Loop** activities) that could be fueling dissent. 2) **Total Freeze Log:** Track compliance with the **Total Freeze** on all non-volume focused activities. **Feedback Loop:** Rumors trigger an immediate threat of a **Financial Audit** and the invocation of the **Financial Penalty Clause** against the partner if the rumor is not suppressed. **Iteration Change:** Enforce **Unilateral Mandate** for total **Output-Only Mandate** adherence, forbidding the use of the word 'rumor' or 'trust' in any internal report."}
