{"attribute": "Learning Agility", "question_id": "LA_Q4", "question_text": "Older/low-literacy women felt excluded. Describe how you will observe, learn, and adapt the experience with them (not for them) within one market cycle.", "score": 2, "band_label": "Strategic", "text": "**Observe/Learn:** Use a targeted **Adaptive MEAL Loop Protocol** focusing on **Tier 2 MEAL Signal** (e.g., time-to-transaction, self-reported confidence) for 20 low-literacy women. Collect data via audio diaries, converting their observations into co-owned **TOWS Matrix Review** inputs. **Adapt:** The collected **Evidence-Based Learning** triggers a formal **Flexible Variance Policy** pivot, co-signed in the **Decision Log**, to dedicate 10% of field agent time specifically to low-literacy peer support, formalized in the **RACI Chart** (Shared Responsibility). **Market Cycle Output:** A co-signed **Joint Narrative Statement** that uses the women’s quotes to justify the FVP pivot, demonstrating **Shared Accountability** for **Mission Fidelity**."}
{"attribute": "Learning Agility", "question_id": "LA_Q4", "question_text": "Older/low-literacy women felt excluded. Describe how you will observe, learn, and adapt the experience with them (not for them) within one market cycle.", "score": 1, "band_label": "Compliant", "text": "**Observe/Learn:** Conduct a simple 'time-and-motion' study comparing the new **Busoga audio consent** flow with the old text-based flow, specifically tracking the **Administrative Overhead** associated with troubleshooting for older users. **Adapt:** Implement **Procedural Fixes** by mandating that all field agents use the **MEAL Jargon Glossary** to simplify explanations, and adopt the **Simplified Compliance Checklist** for the micro-loan process. **Market Cycle Output:** A memo confirming **Grants Disbursement Approval** is expedited for all applications that follow the streamlined **Procedural Standardization** for audio consent, showing **Administrative Simplicity** and **Compliance Stability**."}
{"attribute": "Learning Agility", "question_id": "LA_Q4", "question_text": "Older/low-literacy women felt excluded. Describe how you will observe, learn, and adapt the experience with them (not for them) within one market cycle.", "score": 0, "band_label": "Counterproductive", "text": "**Observe/Learn:** **Formal Partner Lead** conducts a centralized **Staff Reorganization** to assign a single, compliance-focused liaison to observe all low-literacy users, with the sole goal of enforcing the **Output-Only Mandate**. **Adapt:** Issue a **Unilateral Mandate** memo removing the **Busoga audio consent** feature, arguing it causes **Execution Drift** and is a distraction from volume targets. **Market Cycle Output:** A report confirming a **Total Freeze** on all low-literacy user innovation funds. The only success metric is adherence to **Output Target Compliance** volume goals, enforced by the threat of a **Financial Penalty Clause**."}
{"attribute": "Learning Agility", "question_id": "LA_Q4", "question_text": "Older/low-literacy women felt excluded. Describe how you will observe, learn, and adapt the experience with them (not for them) within one market cycle.", "score": 3, "band_label": "Transformative", "text": "**Observe/Learn:** Use **Strategic Dissent Dialogue** as the core learning tool. Kujenga women lead peer observations of the transaction process, focusing on points where the system reinforces **Organizational Aversion to Local Wisdom**. **Adapt:** The findings are logged in a **Contradiction Log** as evidence against the **Centralized Logframe Design**'s assumption of high digital literacy. The team co-signs an **Audit-Ready Innovation** mandate to prototype a token-based system. **Market Cycle Output:** A **Localization Maturity Index (LMI)** report is created, showcasing the basic-phone flow as a **Model Ownership** success and a **Policy Prototype** for other regions, proving **System Engagement**."}
{"attribute": "Learning Agility", "question_id": "LA_Q4", "question_text": "Older/low-literacy women felt excluded. Describe how you will observe, learn, and adapt the experience with them (not for them) within one market cycle.", "score": 2, "band_label": "Strategic", "text": "**Observe/Learn:** The older women form a 'Micro-Design Working Group' with **Decision Authority (D-A)** over the **basic-phone/offline** UI/UX. The group uses a co-owned **Gender Audit Protocol** to identify friction points related to safety and access. **Adapt:** The D-A group mandates the use of larger, simplified fonts and a one-step USSD menu. The rationale for the redesign is formally recorded in the **Decision Log**, showing the impact of the **Governance Clarity** model. **Market Cycle Output:** A **Contingency Planning Protocol** is co-created with the working group, ensuring the low-literacy experience is protected in case of future network failures, formalizing **Structured Risk Mitigation**."}
{"attribute": "Learning Agility", "question_id": "LA_Q4", "question_text": "Older/low-literacy women felt excluded. Describe how you will observe, learn, and adapt the experience with them (not for them) within one market cycle.", "score": 1, "band_label": "Compliant", "text": "**Observe/Learn:** Field agents use the **Standardized Quality Check Card** to track transaction completion time for older/low-literacy users. This data pinpoints the most complex step in the flow. **Adapt:** Implement **Procedural Fixes** by mandating that all field agents use the **MEAL Jargon Glossary** to simplify explanations, and adopt the **Simplified Compliance Checklist** for the micro-loan process. **Market Cycle Output:** The new training materials and the low transaction error rate (proving **Budget Adherence Proven**) are submitted to Grants as the primary evidence of successful **Procedural Consistency**, reducing **Administrative Rigidity**."}
{"attribute": "Learning Agility", "question_id": "LA_Q4", "question_text": "Older/low-literacy women felt excluded. Describe how you will observe, learn, and adapt the experience with them (not for them) within one market cycle.", "score": 0, "band_label": "Counterproductive", "text": "**Observe/Learn:** A centralized team observes the women to identify which ones are causing the most **Administrative Workload Escalation** due to their low-literacy. **Adapt:** Implement **Punitive Control** by requiring these women to only transact during off-peak hours, streamlining the overall volume to eliminate **Execution Drift**. **Market Cycle Output:** A memo is issued by the **Formal Partner Lead** enforcing **Unilateral Mandate** of the new schedule, prioritizing the political need for high **Output Target Compliance** over inclusivity, ensuring **Control Imposition**."}
{"attribute": "Learning Agility", "question_id": "LA_Q4", "question_text": "Older/low-literacy women felt excluded. Describe how you will observe, learn, and adapt the experience with them (not for them) within one market cycle.", "score": 3, "band_label": "Transformative", "text": "**Observe/Learn:** Initiate a **Mutual Partnership Reset** by co-funding a **Peer Learning** exchange where low-literacy women train the lead developer on their daily context. The goal is to establish **Authentic Collaboration**. **Adapt:** The developer uses this learning to formally draft a **Contradiction Log** entry against the existing system, arguing that the technical design is the source of exclusion. **Market Cycle Output:** The team co-signs a mandate to eliminate all unnecessary technical terms from the user interface and replace them with **Community-Defined Outcomes** language, achieving **Transparent Ownership** of the user experience and increasing **Institutional Credibility Score**."}
{"attribute": "Learning Agility", "question_id": "LA_Q4", "question_text": "Older/low-literacy women felt excluded. Describe how you will observe, learn, and adapt the experience with them (not for them) within one market cycle.", "score": 2, "band_label": "Strategic", "text": "**Observe/Learn:** Use a **Structured Learning** approach. Kujenga women lead ethnographic observation sessions, documenting which physical cues or simplified icons are needed for transaction success. The raw observations are classified as **Tier 2 MEAL Signal** data. **Adapt:** The collected data is used to justify a reallocation of **Contingency Planning Protocol** funds to purchase durable, locally relevant instructional signage. **Market Cycle Output:** The reallocation decision is documented in the **Decision Log**, proving the direct link between **Evidence-Based Learning** and adaptive resource allocation, establishing **Governance Clarity**."}
{"attribute": "Learning Agility", "question_id": "LA_Q4", "question_text": "Older/low-literacy women felt excluded. Describe how you will observe, learn, and adapt the experience with them (not for them) within one market cycle.", "score": 1, "band_label": "Compliant", "text": "**Observe/Learn:** Field agents use a simple verbal Q&A to check for **Jargon Confusion** post-transaction. The most frequently confused terms are compiled. **Adapt:** The confused terms are eliminated or replaced by simpler **linguistic workarounds** in all **Standardized Training Materials**. **Market Cycle Output:** The new training materials are rolled out, and the transaction error rate is tracked to ensure **Procedural Consistency** and **Compliance Stability**. The goal is to reduce confusion without triggering **Administrative Rigidity**."}
{"attribute": "Learning Agility", "question_id": "LA_Q4", "question_text": "Older/low-literacy women felt excluded. Describe how you will observe, learn, and adapt the experience with them (not for them) within one market cycle.", "score": 0, "band_label": "Counterproductive", "text": "**Observe/Learn:** The **Formal Partner Lead** conducts a **Financial Audit** of all spending related to local training materials, identifying this spending as a threat to **Control Prioritization**. **Adapt:** Issue a **Unilateral Mandate** requiring the immediate stop of all local design work and the centralization of all training material production under the Formal Partner. **Market Cycle Output:** A memo is issued mandating **Control Imposition** and total adherence to the **Output-Only Mandate**, eliminating any budget lines for **Sensitive Advocacy Pivot** activities (like local gender-specific training)."
{"attribute": "Learning Agility", "question_id": "LA_Q4", "question_text": "Older/low-literacy women felt excluded. Describe how you will observe, learn, and adapt the experience with them (not for them) within one market cycle.", "score": 3, "band_label": "Transformative", "text": "**Observe/Learn:** The team uses the exclusion as a catalyst for a **Strategic Dissent Dialogue**, where the lead developer spends 3 days in the field, using only a basic phone. This forces direct experience with the excluded flow. **Adapt:** The developer's learning drives the creation of a **Contradiction Log** entry against the tech-centric logframe. **Adaptation** is achieved by co-designing a **Peer Learning** training model where experienced basic-phone users are paid as trainers. **Market Cycle Output:** The **Capacity Transfer Plan (CTP)** is signed, making experienced users **Model Ownership** experts and proving the shift from **Organizational Aversion to Local Wisdom** to **System Engagement**."}
